         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[In Colonel Mitchell's  ¶ Journal of an Expedition into the Interior of Tropical Australia  ¶ (1848) is a drawing and a brief reference to a "tree without branches, the leaves of which hang gracefully...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.04.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">To the Gardeners' Chronicle and Agricultural Gazette</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. For the text given here, see </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle and agricultural gazette</seg>., 7 June 1873, p. 775. The letter is dated to mid-April as the latest likely date that it could have been sent to have been included in this issue.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[In Colonel Mitchell's </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of an Expedition into the Interior of Tropical Australia </seg>
               <seg style="">(1848) is a drawing and a brief reference to a "tree without branches, the leaves of which hang gracefully around the stem, giving it the appearance of the plume of a staff officer, on which account the tree or shrub has been known as the </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Plume Bush</seg>
               <seg style="">."</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mitchell (1848), p. 219. The illustration from Mitchell is inserted at this point.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> It has been a matter of interest ever since to know what this could be, but the mystery has been recently solved by Baron </seg>
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">von Mueller</seg>
               <seg style="">, who writes us that he has just received fruits of the plant from Brisbane, by which he is enabled to identify it as <name key="Astrotricha%20pterocarpa">Astrotricha pterocarpa</name>, which is described among the <name key="Araliaceae">Araliaceae</name> in Bentham's</seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> Flora Australiensis</seg>
               <seg style="">, iii. 379.</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">] </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Araliaceae">Araliaceae</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Astrotricha%20pterocarpa">Astrotricha pterocarpa</name>
            </p>
